  "steps": [
    "Heat mustard oil in a pan till it begins to smoke. Add green cardamoms, cloves, black cardamoms, cinnamon and bay leaf, mix and sauté till fragrant.",
    "Add onions, mix and sauté till translucent. Add mutton, ginger-garlic paste, Mathania chilli paste and salt and mix well. Add Mathania dried red chillies, mix well and sear on high heat for 5-6 minutes.",
    "Meanwhile, take yogurt in a bowl, add turmeric powder, red chilli powder and coriander powder and whisk well. Add ¼ cup water and mix well.",
    "Add yogurt mixture to the pan and mix well. Cook on high heat for 8-10 minutes or till oil separates.",
    "Rinse the bowl with 2½ cups water and add to the pan. Mix well and once the mixture comes to a boil, add salt and mix well. Lower the heat, cover and cook for 45-50 minutes.",
    "Place a bowl with hot coal in the middle of the pan and drizzle 1 tablespoon ghee. Cover immediately for 1 minute.",
    "Remove the cover and take away the bowl with hot coal. Add 2 tablespoons ghee, mix well and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Transfer into a serving bowl, garnish with coriander sprig and serve hot with bajra rotis."
  ],
